The paper proposes a method for interpreting the contributions of input features in classification models, which is a common problem in machine learning. The method is specifically applied to electroencephalogram (EEG) datasets, which suggests a focus on neural networks and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
